<p>I've many buttons on my Activity, and I've also an onTouchEvent listener to detect double touch. I'm able to double touch only in a zone where there are no other views (like buttons, imagebuttons and so on), because these views have a onTouchListener. So, how can I give an higher priority to the double touch? I need to avoid the onTouchListener when the onTouchEvent occur.</p>  <p>Here is my onTouchEvent function:</p>  <pre><code>public boolean onTouchEvent(MotionEvent event){     int action = event.getAction() &amp; MotionEvent.ACTION_MASK;      if (action == MotionEvent.ACTION_POINTER_DOWN) {         if (speedMenuStatus) {             speedMenuTranslation = (AnimatorSet) AnimatorInflater.loadAnimator(getApplicationContext(), R.anim.speed_menu_translation_up);             speedMenuTranslation.setTarget(speedMenu);             speedMenuTranslation.start();             System.out.println("ON");              speedMenuStatus = false;          } else {             speedMenuTranslation = (AnimatorSet) AnimatorInflater.loadAnimator(getApplicationContext(), R.anim.speed_menu_translation_down);             speedMenuTranslation.setTarget(speedMenu);             speedMenuTranslation.start();             System.out.println("DOWN");              speedMenu.bringToFront();              speedMenuStatus = true;         }         return true;     }     return false;  } </code></pre>  <p>And this is an example of one of my buttons with onTouchListener:</p>  <pre><code>box.boxButton.setOnTouchListener(new View.OnTouchListener() {//eccolo             @Override             public boolean onTouch(View v, MotionEvent event) {                 if(event.getAction() == event.ACTION_DOWN) {                     // Some code here....                     return true;                 }                  return false;             }          }); </code></pre>